1. Install the umbrello application found in the kdesdk RPM. Version 3.5.10 is
   the minimum required version! This version cannot be found in the CERN
   software repository but can be downloaded from:

   http://apt.kde-redhat.org/apt/kde-redhat/redhat/el5/x86_64/RPMS.stable/

   The RPMS required from this repository are:
   - kdebindings-dcopperl-3.5.10-1.el5.x86_64.rpm
   - kde-filesystem-4-1.noarch.rpm
   - kdelibs-3.5.10-1.el5.x86_64.rpm
   - kdelibs-devel-3.5.10-1.el5.x86_64.rpm
   - kdepim-devel-3.5.10-2.el5.x86_64.rpm
   - kdesdk-3.5.10-1.el5.x86_64.rpm
   - kde-settings-3.5-18.fc6.noarch.rpm
   - kde-settings-kdm-3.5-18.fc6.noarch.rpm
   - xorg-x11-xdm-1.0.5-5.fc6.x86_64.rpm

   All other dependencies can be resolved using the standard Quattor SLC5
   repository: http://swrep/swrep/x86_64_slc5/

   [root@lxcastordev04 waldron]# rpm -Uvh *.rpm
