   After successful installation, `/usr/bin/umbrello` should work out of the box
   without any modifications.

2. To compile gencastor, download and extract the kdesdk source files from:

   http://www.linuxfromscratch.org/blfs/view/svn/kde/kdesdk.html

   Note: Make sure its version 3.5.10!

   [lxcastordev04 src]# wget http://mirrors.isc.org/pub/kde/stable/3.5.10/src/kdesdk-3.5.10.tar.bz2
   2010-11-05 16:09:25 (1.45 MB/s) - `kdesdk-3.5.10.tar.bz2' saved [5252055/5252055]
   [lxcastordev04 src]# bunzip2 kdesdk-3.5.10.tar.bz2
   [lxcastordev04 src]# tar -xf kdesdk-3.5.10.tar

3. Compile the umbrello code from the kdesdk source (Some objects are required
   to compile gencastor!)

   Notes:
     - If you get a ./configure warning about Subversion libraries, ignore it!
     - Compiling umbrello takes a long time!

   [root@lxcastordev04 src]# cd kdesdk-3.5.10
   [root@lxcastordev04 kdesdk-3.5.10]# ./configure
   [root@lxcastordev04 kdesdk-3.5.10]# cd umbrello/
   [root@lxcastordev04 umbrello]# make

4. Compile the gencastor code from the appropriate SVN location e.g. Trunk,
   v2_1_9Version branch, v2_1_9_9 tag etc...

   [root@lxcastordev04 trunk]# cd codeGeneration/gencastor/
   [root@lxcastordev04 trunk]# export PATH=$PATH:/usr/lib64/qt-3.3/bin/
   [root@lxcastordev04 trunk]# export CASTOR_ROOT=<path to castor root directory>
   [root@lxcastordev04 trunk]# export UMBRELLOBASE=<path to kdesdk source files>
   [root@lxcastordev04 gencastor]# make

   At the end of the make process you should have a gencastor.bin binary.
